 B. |year=1993 |title=Herodotus, Book II |series=\u00c9tudes pr\u00e9liminaires aux religions orientales dans l'Empire romain |volume=43 |publisher=Brill |location=Leiden |isbn=978-90-04-07737-9 |ref=harv}}\n* Majumdar, R.C. (1981). The Classical accounts of India: Being a compilation of the English translations of the accounts left by Herodotus, Megasthenes, Arrian, Strabo, Quintus, Diodorus, Siculus, Justin, Plutarch, Frontinus, Nearchus, Apollonius, Pliny, Ptolemy, Aelian, and others with maps. Calcutta: Firma KLM. {{ISBN|978-0-8364-0704-4}}\n* {{cite book |last=Marincola |first=John |year=2001 |title=Greek Historians |publisher=Oxford University Press |isbn=978-0-19-922501-9 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Mikalson |first=Jon D. |year=2003 |title=Herodotus and Religion in the Persian Wars |publisher=Univ of North Carolina Press |location=Chapel Hill, NC |isbn=978-0-8078-2798-7 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Murray |first=Oswyn |year=1986 |chapter=Greek historians |pages=[https://archive.org/details/oxfordhistoryofc00john/page/186 186\u2013203] |title=The Oxford History of the Classical World |editor-first1=John |editor-last1=Boardman |editor-first2=Jasper |editor-last2=Griffin |editor-first3=Oswyn |editor-last3=Murray |publisher=Oxford University Press |isbn=978-0-19-872112-3 |ref=harv |chapter-url=https://archive.org/details/oxfordhistoryofc00john/page/186 }}\n* {{cite book |last=Nielsen |first=Flemming A.J. |year=1997 |title=The Tragedy in History: Herodotus and the Deuteronomistic History |publisher=A&C Black |isbn=978-1-85075-688-0 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Peissel |first=Michel |authorlink=Michel Peissel |year=1984 |title=The Ants' Gold: The Discovery of the Greek El Dorado in the Himalayas |publisher=Collins |isbn=978-0-00-272514-9 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Rawlinson |first=George |year=1859 |title=The History of Herodotus |volume=1 |publisher=D. Appleton and Company |location=New York |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Roberts |first=Jennifer T. |year=2011 |title=Herodotus: a Very Short Introduction |publisher=OXford University Press |isbn=978-0-19-957599-2 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Romm |first=James |year=1998 |title=Herodotus |publisher=Yale University Press |location=New Haven, CT |isbn=978-0-300-07229-7 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal |last=Saltzman |first=Joe |year=2010 |title=Herodotus as an ancient journalist: reimagining antiquity's historians as journalists |journal=[[The IJPC Journal]] |volume=2 |pages=153\u2013185 |url=http://ijpc.uscannenberg.org/journal/index.php/ijpcjournal/article/viewFile/22/29 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Sparks |first=Kenton L. |year=1998 |title=Ethnicity and Identity in Ancient Israel: Prolegomena to the Study of Ethnic Sentiments and their Expression in the Hebrew Bible |publisher=Eisenbrauns |location=Winona Lake, IN |isbn=978-1-57506-033-0 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal |last=Wardman |first=A.E. |year=1960 |title=Myth in Greek historiography |journal=[[Historia: Zeitschrift f\u00fcr Alte Geschichte]] |volume=9 |issue=4 |pages=403\u2013413 |jstor=4434671 |ref=harv}}\n* {{Cite book |last=Waters |first=K.H. |year=1985 |title=Herodotos the Historian: His Problems, Methods and Originality |publisher = University of Oklahoma Press |isbn=978-0-8061-1928-1 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Welsby |first=Derek |year=1996 |title=The Kingdom of Kush |publisher=British Museum Press |location=London |isbn=978-0-7141-0986-2 |ref=harv}}\n{{Refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{refbegin|32em}}\n* {{cite book |editor1-last=Bakker |editor1-first=Egbert J. |editorlink1=Egbert Bakker |editor2-last=de Jong |editor2-first=Irene J.F. |editor3-last=van Wees |editor3-first=Hans |title=Brill's companion to Herodotus |year=2002 |publisher=E.J. Brill |location=Leiden |isbn=978-90-04-12060-0}}\n* {{cite book |last=Baragwanath |first=Emily |year=2010 |title=Motivation and Narrative in Herodotus |series=Oxford Classical Monographs |publisher=Oxford University Press |isbn=978-0-19-964550-3 